\c 16
\p
\v 1 A mitkam of David:
\q1 Keep me\f + M, S, Q, Impv.\f* O God because I have sought refuge\f + 1, C, S, Q, Per.\f* in you.
\q1
\v 2 I have said\f + 1, C, S, Q, Per. Looks like 2fs--check.\f* to YHWH,
\q1 "You are Lord,
\q1 my good is not outside of you.
\q1
\v 3 For holy ones who are in the land,
\q1 And mighty ones, all my delight is in them.\f + Ps 15:4.\f*
\q1
\v 4 Their pain shall increase, they hurry after another\f + ESV, NRSV: "another god." Cf. Ps 24:4?\f*,
\q1 I will not pour out their drink offering from blood,
\q1 And I will not lift up their name on my lips.
\q1
\v 5 YHWH is the portion of my share and my cup,
\q1 You hold on to my lot.
\q1
\v 6 Lines fall for me in pleasant places,
\q1 Indeed my inheritance is pleasant to me.
\q1
\v 7 I will bless YHWH who counsels me,
\q1 Even by night my inmost part instructs me.
\q1
\v 8 I have placed YHWH before me continually,
\q1 Because he is at my right hand I will not waver.\f + Ps 15:5c.\f*
\q1
\v 9 Therefore my heart is glad,
\q1 And my glory shouts with joy,
\q1 Even my flesh will dwell in safety.
\q1
\v 10 For you will not abandon my life to Sheol,
\q1 You will not let your faithful see the pit.
\q1
\v 11 You make known to me the way of life,
\q1 Plenty of joy is with your face,\f + Ps 15:1; 24:3.\f*
\q1 Pleasant things are at your right hand forever.